sub_title: Project Manager MENA, CIB at VNG-I | MSc IR with a focus on Political Economy and the Middle East  | MA Middle Eastern Studies
summary: Project Manager and Development Economist, graduate of the MSc International Relations of the Middle East at the University of Edinburgh, as well as the MA Middle Eastern Studies at the University of Groningen, with an academic interest in the political economies of Iraq, Iran and the Gulf Region. Having been described as a team player and an organiser, I'm an engaged professional, with experience working in project management, on research projects and in leadership positions. I'm always planning on extending my knowledge and broadening my horizons by joining additional programmes, following extra courses, and engaging in further explorations in fields I find interesting, and by taking on challenges along the way.
